use to stop the autoplay of animated .gif files and to add a play button on top of them

repo: https://github.com/krasimir/gifffer
clone: cloned repository to local: /Users/statmike/github/gifffer
copy: /Users/statmike/github/gifffer/build/gifffer.min.js
paste: /Users/statmike/github/statmike.github.io/js/gifffer.min.js

created _includes/gifffer.html

added {% include gifffer.html %} to _layouts/post.html 

in _data/settings.yml change ajax_loading: true to ajax_loading: false
    this seems to fix the .gif files not loading unless the page is refreshed...

USAGE:
for pages where you want to use this (blog post, projects, ...)
    add images with the IMG tag:
        <img data-gifffer="/images/blog/sgf2020/Slide 9.gif">
        

